<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
In MHD_get_timeout64, the loop variable is declared as a non-const pointer: "struct MHD_Connection *pos;". In the following code pos is only used to read members (pos->connection_timeout_ms, pos->last_activity, pos = pos->prevX) and is never used to modify the pointed-to object. Therefore pos could (and per Rule 8.13 should) be declared to point to a const-qualified type, e.g. "const struct MHD_Connection *pos;". As written, this violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13.
</scenario>
